</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64541911"><p>I love how the article has to call out female "wage gap" harming what is still some of the highest paid workers in the world.  When many major companies have done investigations to make sure that they weren't underpaying their female engineers - only to discover that they were underpaying male engineers instead.</p><p>The "wage gap" isn't from companies paying women less for the same work - it's that women make different choices in work profiles, which costs them raw wages.</p><p>As another poster put it - move out.  The high wages are causing companies to outsource from silicon valley, depressing wages there, but it's still one of the most insanely expensive places to live in the world.  It needs fewer people if nobody is going to fix the housing problems (which I view as mostly politically and NIMBY caused).</p></div>
	</div>

