		<div id="comment_body_64541975"><p><div class="quote"><p>But the story presents itself as being about tech workers - yet the example presented is about someone who works in marketing?</p></div><p>Tech companies don't have a need for marketing?</p><p>The story wasn't specifically about tech workers.  It was about companies in Silicon Valley which could be anything, which is exactly what was stated in the blurb:</p><p><div class="quote"><p> "Today, about every company is a tech company, whether they're in retail, consumer goods or hospitality</p></div><p>The only mention of tech was including companies such as Apple, Meta, and Google who are also laying off people, just like all those other non-tech companies.</p></div>
